The package contains the following:

XComp.C: 
-------
  
   * LEP style compilation of mass measurements
   * To run .L XComp.C    


RooBackPdf.cxx
--------------

   * RooFit class to parameterize the background in X, psi(2S) events
   * \left(m - m_r \right) ^{c0}  \cdot \textrm{exp} \left( -c1 \cdot m - c2 \cdot m^2 \right)
   * To compile (interactively): .L RooBackPdf.cxx+


RooPsi2m.cxx
--------------

   * RooFit class to parameterize the background
   * Parameterize the pipi mass spectrum in Psi(2S) (work for the Y as well)
   * constructor is : 
       RooPsi2m ppModel= RooPsi2m("psi2", "psi2", x, mJpsi, mpsi2, mPi , lambda);
       // lambda fixed to one (normal) is pure S-Wave
       // For the other resonances you need to set mJpsi and mpsi2 appropriately 
   * To compile (interactively): .L RooPsi2m.cxx+

* xtoy.C
--------

   * Toy MC for sensitivity to X Mass.
   * Signal model: Voightian, Background Model: RooBackPdf (parameters from same sign data)
   * To run at command line: .L xtoy.C; xtoy("output.root", nSignal, nBack) 